The paper deals with the metric capacitated facility location problem, which is a well-studied problem in theoretical computer science and optimization. The paper discusses the limitations of linear programming relaxations for this problem and provides lower bounds on the size of approximate formulations. Based on this, the most likely sub-categories are cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory), cs.CC (Computational Complexity), cs.LG (Machine Learning), and cs.IT (Information Theory).
